      • fileName

      • fileDurationMs

        public long fileDurationMs
        Duration of input audio file in milliseconds

      • frequencyResolution

        public double frequencyResolution
        Frequency resolution of FFT result. This is calculated by dividing the audio file's sampling rate by the number of points in the FFT. A lower frequency resolution makes it easier to distinguish between frequencies that are close together. By improving frequency resolution, however, some time resolution is lost because there are fewer FFT calculations per unit of time (sampling windows are larger).

      • windowDurationMs

        public long windowDurationMs
        Length of each sampling window in milliseconds. This is proportional to the length of each window in terms of number of samples.

        The parameters used to compute this FFT.
